TransitionProtocol

public protocol TransitionProtocol : TimelineProtocol

The TransitionProtocol protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ClutterTransition instance. The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below. For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see Transition. Alternatively, use TransitionRef as a lighweight, unowned reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.

The ClutterTransition structure contains private data and should only be accessed using the provided API.

  • ptr

    Untyped pointer to the underlying ClutterTransition instance.

    Declaration

    Swift

    var ptr: UnsafeMutableRawPointer { get }
    Show on GitHub
  • transition_ptr Default implementation

    Typed pointer to the underlying ClutterTransition instance.

    Default Implementation

    Return the stored, untyped pointer as a typed pointer to the ClutterTransition instance.

    Declaration

    Swift

    var transition_ptr: UnsafeMutablePointer<ClutterTransition> { get }

  • set(animatable:) Extension method

    Sets the ClutterTransition:animatable property.

    The transition will acquire a reference to the animatable instance, and will call the ClutterTransitionClass.attached() virtual function.

    If an existing ClutterAnimatable is attached to transition, the reference will be released, and the ClutterTransitionClass.detached() virtual function will be called.

    Declaration

    Swift

    func set(animatable: AnimatableProtocol)
    Show on GitHub
  • setFrom(value:) Extension method

    Sets the initial value of the transition.

    This is a convenience function that will either create the ClutterInterval used by transition, or will update it if the ClutterTransition:interval is already set.

    This function will copy the contents of value, so it is safe to call g_value_unset() after it returns.

    If transition already has a ClutterTransition:interval set, then value must hold the same type, or a transformable type, as the interval’s ClutterInterval:value-type property.

    This function is meant to be used by language bindings.

    Declaration

    Swift

    func setFrom(value: GLibObject.ValueProtocol)
    Show on GitHub
  • set(interval:) Extension method

    Sets the ClutterTransition:interval property using interval.
